article.headline: Milwaukee routs Oakland 86-64
article.story: MILWAUKEE -- Jordan Aaron hit five 3-pointers and finished with 23 points as UW-Milwaukee beat Oakland 86-64 on Sunday. Oakland's Travis Bader set the NCAA Division I record for the most career 3-pointers, surpassing the previous mark of 457 set by Duke's J.J. Redick. Bader, who entered the game two behind Redick, missed his first 3-point attempt but made his next four. He broke the record with a shot from the right corner with 6:17 left in the first half, pulling Oakland within 29-28. Despite Bader's record-breaking performance, Milwaukee (15-9, 5-5 Horizon League) outshot the Golden Grizzlies (9-15, 4-5) from 3-point range. The Panthers were 13 of 25, while Oakland finished 10 of 21. Matt Tiby was one of five Milwaukee players in double figures with 10 points and 17 rebounds. Bader had 21 for Oakland.
